    "122175288": {
      "title": "The excess of sets of complex exponentials",
      "abstract": "Let A=f{A2} be a complex sequence and denote its associated set of complex exponentials {exp(iA2x)} by e(A). Redheffer and Alexander have shown that if > I-AnnI < ?O then e(A) and e(y) have the same excess over their common completeness interval. This paper shows this result to be the best possible."
